# versions.env — pinned inputs + trust anchors for mlbuild.sh
#
# This file is SOURCED by mlbuild.sh (treat it as code, not data — AUDIT F3).
# It pins the *durable* trust anchors: upstream versions and PGP key
# FINGERPRINTS.  Per-version content hashes are NOT pinned here — they are
# auto-derived into versions.lock on the first verified build (see plan §6.0).
#
# Trust model (plan §6.0 / §8): authenticity comes from a signature made by a
# key we vendored OUT-OF-BAND (keys/, fingerprints below), never from a
# checksum fetched alongside the tarball.  See keys/README.md.

# ── Upstream versions ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Example pins — bump to a current LTS/release and re-verify per keys/README.md.
LINUX_VER=6.12.30          # a 6.12.x LTS
LINUX_MAJOR=v6.x           # cdn.kernel.org path component
BUSYBOX_VER=1.36.1         # NOTE: tc.c needs the CONFIG_TC disable vs kernel >=6.8; 1.37.0 fixes it
UROOT_REF=v0.14.0          # faithful track (§11); Go-module ref, integrity via go.sum
GO_VER=1.22.5              # faithful track; Go toolchain (see Containerfile)
GO_SHA256=904b924d435eaea086515bc63235b192ea441bd8c9b198c507e85009e6e4c7f0   # go${GO_VER}.linux-amd64.tar.gz (dl.google.com)

# ── PGP keyrings (vendored) + the fingerprint each MUST contain ──────────────
# Paths are relative to micro-linux/.  Fingerprints are 40 hex chars, no spaces.
# Obtain + verify these out-of-band, then paste the fingerprint here. mlbuild.sh
# refuses to build until they are real (the PIN-ME sentinel fails closed).
KERNEL_KEYRING=keys/kernel.gpg
# Greg Kroah-Hartman + Sasha Levin (kernel.org stable signers; a point release
# may be signed by either). Verified via kernel.org WKD AND cross-checked
# against kernel.org/category/signatures.html (two channels). See keys/README.md.
KERNEL_FPR="647F28654894E3BD457199BE38DBBDC86092693E E27E5D8A3403A2EF66873BBCDEA66FF797772CDC"
BUSYBOX_KEYRING=keys/busybox.gpg
# Denys Vlasenko (busybox release signer; key-id read from the release .sig).
# WEAKER out-of-band verification than the kernel keys — busybox has no
# authoritative fingerprint page; cross-check independently. See keys/README.md.
BUSYBOX_FPR=C9E9416F76E610DBD09D040F47B70C55ACC9965B

# ── Container base image — PINNED BY DIGEST (AUDIT F5) ───────────────────────
# Refresh with:  podman pull debian:bookworm-slim && \
#                podman image inspect debian:bookworm-slim --format '{{index .RepoDigests 0}}'
#          (or:  skopeo inspect docker://debian:bookworm-slim --format '{{.Digest}}')
BASE_IMAGE="debian:bookworm-slim@sha256:0104b334637a5f19aa9c983a91b54c89887c0984081f2068983107a6f6c21eeb"

# ── Reproducible builds (plan §8) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Pin the kernel's build identity + a fixed timestamp, and busybox's build date,
# so the artifacts embed nothing machine- or time-specific.  Combined with the
# digest-pinned toolchain above and the sorted / uid-gid-0 / mtime-0 / gzip -n
# cpio, two independent builders get byte-identical kernel + initramfs.  That is
# the only real mitigation for the §6.0 residual (a compromised upstream signing
# key): many parties rebuild from the pinned source and attest the same hash.
# SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH is the cross-tool reproducible-builds standard (busybox honors
# it directly; mlbuild derives KBUILD_BUILD_TIMESTAMP from it for the kernel).
# Arbitrary but FIXED — bump freely, just keep it committed so rebuilds match.
SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH=1700000000      # 2023-11-14T22:13:20Z
KBUILD_BUILD_USER=mklab
KBUILD_BUILD_HOST=micro-linux
